SIMPLE: collaborate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: collaborate
<hw>col*lab"o*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>to work together with another toward a common goal, especially in
an intellectual endeavor; <as>as, four chemists <ex>collaborated</ex> on
the synthesis of the compound; three authors <ex>collaborated</ex> in
writing the book</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to willingly cooperate with an enemy, especially an
enemy nation occupying one's own country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Collaborateur</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
